sarvar ityādi. yasmād asau sarveṣām ātmani dharmadhātau vedakatvena sthitaḥ, tasmāt sarvaḥ.

<commentary>satsukhatvenety anāsravadhruvottamasukhatvena. bodhanād rater iti tasyaiva niruttarasya sukhasya vedanād yo hi taṃ na vedayate, nidrāṇa evāsau. brahmāditvaṃ yad uddiṣṭaṃ tad iyatā nirdiṣṭam—deha ityādinā. anyad apy āha sa eva devatā dehasambhavād ity arthaḥ. pūrvapade halopaḥ, uttarapade sambhalopaḥ. svārthe talā deva eva devatā. dehasambhavatvena sulabhatvam asya sūcayati.</commentary>

buddhaḥ sa iti saṃbuddha ity arthaḥ.
